# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CODEOWNERS — Automatic Review Requirements
#
# GitHub automatically requests a review from the listed owner(s) whenever a
# pull request modifies a file matching that pattern.  Rules are matched in
# order from LAST to FIRST, so more-specific patterns below override broader
# ones above.
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Syntax:  <pattern>  <@owner-or-team> [<@additional-owner> ...]
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Default owner for everything not matched below ───────────────────────────
# Remove or replace with a specific team if you don't want a catch-all.
# *   @gke-labs-team

# ── Infrastructure — Terraform ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Any change under terraform/ (modules, environments, provider configs)
# requires review from the infra/platform team.
/terraform/                         @gke-labs-team

# ── Application delivery — Helm ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Helm chart changes affect live deployments; require team sign-off.
/helm/                              @gke-labs-team

# ── CI/CD pipelines & repo configuration ─────────────────────────────────────
# Workflow files and GitHub config can escalate privileges or modify deployments;
# these should never be auto-approved.
/.github/                           @gke-labs-team

# ── Docker images ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Changes to Dockerfiles or the docker/ directory affect the built artifact.
/docker/                            @gke-labs-team

# ── Documentation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Docs changes have a lighter touch — no required reviewer, just FYI.
# /docs/                            @gke-labs-team

# ── Example: specialised sub-team ownership ───────────────────────────────────
# If you have a dedicated security team that owns scanning config:
# /terraform/modules/security/      @gke-labs-security-team
# /.github/workflows/ci.yml        @gke-labs-security-team @gke-labs-team
